{
  "stem": "13469.8",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And from-- after I came back here-- it was very interesting, especially for my daughter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She really was impressed with the whole event.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "When we came back, the synagogue-- my synagogue asked, tell us about it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "What was it like?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we had an evening meeting [INAUDIBLE], and I gave a talk about returning to Belsen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And everybody thought it was very good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it got written up and other people got to hear about it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then somebody said, would you mind giving it to my Rotary Club?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I said, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then I gave the talk to the Rotary Club.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I expanded the talk from not only return to Belsen, but also Belsen during the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I started giving these talks either about Belsen or Belsen and Buckingham Palace and all those sort of things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it grew and grew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I started giving the talks to college students and then to schools.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And now, because the Holocaust is part of the curriculum, history curriculum, more and more schools are now inviting survivors to talk about their experiences.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and I go around there and I do it, often on behalf of the Spiral Institute, sometimes on behalf of friends or colleagues, people that I meet, but most often now in conjunction with Stephen Smith from the Beth Shalom Holocaust-- not Museum, Exhibition, Memorial Centre in Laxton near Nottingham, and that started last year.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I'm very much involved with him, very much appreciate the work that he's done, and very keen to collaborate with him and talk to students.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he takes me around all over the country to talk to students.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
